msg_object: %1: Transition to state '%2' (AL Status Code = 0x0070 Detected module ident list does not match).
Reason: The EtherCAT slave has unexpectedly changed its state. Detected module ident list (0xF030) and configured module ident list (0xF050) do not match.
Effect: The operation of the EtherCAT segment is restricted. The operation of the affected EtherCAT slave is not possible.
Solution: Identify reason for the state transition of the slave.

msg_object: %1: SERCOS class1 error occurred: 0x%2 - F2036 Excessive position feedback difference
Reason: An error occurred in the drive control system. Drive signalled a class1-error in state word S-0-0135.
Effect: Drive is set to error state, controller try's to read the diagnosis parameter of the drive.
Solution: Eliminate error reason in drive - it could be caused by the controller (e.g. invalid set values) or by the drive environment (e.g. power supply). The cause can be narrowed by the diagnosis text.
column23: %1......Hardware configuration path or name of drive

msg_object: %1: ER 39-11 %2-%3 (0xFF0C): Fatal error on SDC configuration data detected (error register %4)
Reason: Fatal error on SDC configuration data detected
Solution: Check configuration of the SDC - reload PLC program
column23: %1......Hardware configuration path or name of drive

msg_object: %1: ER 8-155 %2-%3 (0x7300): EtherCAT enc. #2: Backup information not valid (error register %4)

Reason: Encoder #1: (Absolute) position calculation error
Solution: Check line count and encoder gearbox settings. Try switching AbsInitMode to 1.

msg_object: %1: Execute SERCOS command %2 failed (%3C0102 Limit error in parameter (-> S-0-0021), user = %4)
Reason: Execution of a Sercos-command failed. For details see command error code.
Solution: Parameter values must be changed. The cause can be narrowed by the command error code.
column23: %1......Hardware configuration path or name of drive
column26: %4......Calling context. If this parameter 1, the command was triggered by the application, else by the initialization (sercos phase bootup) or error acknowledgment.
